Henry Edwards (actor) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henry_Edwards_(actor) 0 Henry Edwards (18 September 1882 – 2 November 1952) was an English actor and film director. He appeared in 81 films between 1915 and 1952. He also directed 67 films between 1915 and 1937. Edwards was married to actress Chrissie White, who co-starred in a number of his films. He was born in Weston-super-Mare, Somerset and died in Chobham, Surrey. Henry_Edwards ( 18_September_1882 – 2_November_1952 ) was an_English_actor_and_film_director .
